Corliss Palmer https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Corliss_Palmer 0 Corliss Palmer (born July 25, 1899 – August 27, 1952) was an American silent film actress and model. She first came to public attention after winning Motion Picture Magazine's Fame and Fortune Contest in 1920, upon which she was deemed the "most beautiful girl in America." She would go on to appear in a total of sixteen films between 1922 and 1931. Corliss_Palmer ( born July_25_,_1899 – August_27_,_1952 ) was an_American_silent_film_actress_and_model .
